<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77254a4b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s282c"><num value="282c">§ 282c.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are hereby authorized to be appropriated such sums, but not more than $13,575,000 for the acquisition of lands and interests therein and for the development of the San Juan National Historical Park.<ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002059">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002059"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be “San Juan Island National Historical Park.”</note></p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77254a4c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/565/s4">Pub. L. 89–565, § 4</ref>, <date date="1966-09-09">Sept. 9, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/737">80 Stat. 737</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/625/tI/s101/22">Pub. L. 95–625, title I, § 101(22)</ref>, <date date="1978-11-10">Nov. 10, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/3472">92 Stat. 3472</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/88/dA/tI/s118">Pub. L. 111–88, div. A, title I, § 118</ref>, <date date="2009-10-30">Oct. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/2929">123 Stat. 2929</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
